  "title": "Arthritis",
  "source": "arthritis.html",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Systematic ABCDE approach with examples of erosions, osteophytes, joint space, and soft tissue findings."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Source: Radiology Assistant \"Arthritis\" (fractures video lesson). Images are embedded locally."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Approach"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Use a systematic ABCDE approach when evaluating arthritis on radiographs."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Alignment",
        "Bone density (osteopenia/erosions)",
        "Cartilage space (joint space)",
        "Deformity (osteophytes, bone proliferation)",
        "Soft tissue"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "assetId": "asset_cfec87c9db",
      "alt": "Arthritis intro diagram"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "assetId": "asset_151cab3d14",
      "alt": "ABCDE approach to arthritis"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Erosions"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Erosions are focal bone loss at the joint margins-key for inflammatory arthritides."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "assetId": "asset_3c5ad9d764",
      "alt": "Erosions example"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "assetId": "asset_80ea031ffa",
      "alt": "Erosions example 2"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Alignment"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Assess for malalignment and subluxation."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "assetId": "asset_12fdd43f7f",
      "alt": "Alignment reference"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Osteophytes / Deformity"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Bone proliferation and osteophytes are typical in degenerative changes."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "assetId": "asset_eae8e5373a",
      "alt": "Osteophyte reference"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "assetId": "asset_f615b3535e",
      "alt": "Osteophyte reference 2"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Bone Density / Osteopenia"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Periarticular osteopenia suggests inflammatory arthritis; sclerosis favors degenerative disease."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "assetId": "asset_4b7de4320f",
      "alt": "Periarticular osteopenia examples"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Cartilage Space"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Joint space narrowing pattern helps distinguish inflammatory from degenerative disease."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "assetId": "asset_fe59e25ced",
      "alt": "Cartilage/joint space reference"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Soft Tissue"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Evaluate for swelling, effusions, or masses."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "assetId": "asset_a29be7ea35",
      "alt": "Soft tissue reference"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Case: Hand Osteoarthrosis"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Example radiograph showing degenerative changes."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "assetId": "asset_fbfc12453b",
      "alt": "Hand osteoarthrosis"
    }
  ]
}
